and 19 absentees.

23
00:01:35,529 --> 00:01:39,333
The turnout was 97.1%.

24
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:41,101
Because the criteria
weren’t met,

25
00:01:41,134 --> 00:01:43,236
a revote is necessary.

26
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:49,710
Turnout for the most recent vote
in the 13th chairman election

27
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:53,413
has officially exceeded
the 95% quorum.

28
00:01:53,447 --> 00:01:56,283
As a result,
the next election will be held

29
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:59,319
between the 16 candidates
who received the most votes,

30
00:01:59,353 --> 00:02:01,455
so please keep that in mind.

31
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:03,790
And now, without further ado,

32
00:02:03,824 --> 00:02:06,660
I present
the top 16 candidates.

33
00:02:06,693 --> 00:02:09,429
Please make
an informed decision.

34
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:12,499
( Fanfare plays )

35
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:14,702
Pariston hill,
a triple star hunter

36
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:16,337
and current vice-chairman.

37
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:20,074
His motto: "A kinder,
gentler hunter association."

38
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,476
Cheadle Yorkshire,

39
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:25,178
a triple star hunter
and the brains of the zodiacs.

40
00:02:25,212 --> 00:02:28,082
Her motto: "I will
expel all corruption."

41
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:31,551
Leorio paradinight
is a rookie hunter

42
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:34,154
who, after punching ging,
is on the rise.

43
00:02:34,188 --> 00:02:36,490
He is currently studying
to become a doctor.

44
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:40,261
Botobai gigante
is a triple star hunter

45
00:02:40,294 --> 00:02:42,630
as well as an advisor
working with the zodiacs.

46
00:02:42,663 --> 00:02:45,099
He was very close
to the previous chairman.

47
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:49,402
Mizaistom Nana,
a double star crime hunter

48
00:02:49,436 --> 00:02:51,672
and the zodiacs’s conscience,
who has practically

49
00:02:51,705 --> 00:02:54,107
earned the respect
of the anti-chairman faction.

50
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:56,877
Ickshonpe katocha,

51
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:59,379
a single star hacker hunter,

52
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:03,517
a netizen who, even now,
is still refusing to vote.

53
00:03:04,718 --> 00:03:06,153
Teradein neutral,

54
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:08,755
a double star headhunter
and h.R. Specialist.

55
00:03:08,789 --> 00:03:10,791
The keystone of his platform
is his plan

56
00:03:10,824 --> 00:03:13,560
to enact significant reforms
in the hunter exam.

57
00:03:15,229 --> 00:03:16,630
Morel mackernasey,

58
00:03:16,663 --> 00:03:19,299
a single star sea hunter
who defeated the ants

59
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:21,669
and may soon be promoted
to triple star.

60
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,572
He hopes to prepare
for other alien species.

61
00:03:25,672 --> 00:03:27,440
Saccho kobayakawa,

62
00:03:27,474 --> 00:03:30,644
a double star problem hunter
and advisor for the zodiacs.

63
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:32,579
He seeks to reform
the association

64
00:03:32,613 --> 00:03:34,148
from behind the scenes.

65
00:03:35,482 --> 00:03:36,450
Biscuit krueger,

66
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,185
a double star gemstone hunter

67
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:39,519
and the association’s mother--

68
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:42,823
ahem, apologies. Sister figure.

69
00:03:42,856 --> 00:03:45,258
More and more people
want her to scold them.

70
00:03:46,593 --> 00:03:49,362
Sanbica Norton
is a single star virus hunter,

71
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:51,398
as well
as the association’s doctor.

72
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:53,166
Her motto, believe it or not,

73
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,469
is "please,
don’t vote for me."

74
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:57,904
Linne hors-d’oeuvre

75
00:03:57,938 --> 00:03:59,740
is a double star gourmet hunter

76
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:02,175
and the oldest hunter
in the association.

77
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:04,678
No one has heard her speak
for five years.

78
00:04:05,913 --> 00:04:07,681
Bushidora ambitious,

79
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:09,583
a single star blacklist hunter

80
00:04:09,616 --> 00:04:12,452
and member of the association’s
disciplinary committee.

81
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:15,289
He aims to revise the bylaws.

82
00:04:16,557 --> 00:04:17,691
Loupe highland,

83
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:19,593
a lost hunter
who can find anything

84
00:04:19,626 --> 00:04:21,895
from missing contacts
to missing persons.

85
00:04:21,929 --> 00:04:24,498
Currently trying
to locate missing hunters.

86
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:26,834
Cutie beauty,

87
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:29,403
a single star cute hunter
who is recognized

88
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:31,538
as the leader
of the vice-chairman’s fan club.

89
00:04:31,572 --> 00:04:34,708
She also seeks to create
a "cute" association.

90
00:04:36,543 --> 00:04:39,513
Ging freecss,
a double star ruins hunter

91
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:41,815
and vagabond of the zodiacs.

92
00:04:41,849 --> 00:04:44,919
Was it pity votes that put him
back in the running?

93
00:04:51,725 --> 00:04:55,429
Killua: Leorio came in third?
That’s incredible.

94
00:04:57,664 --> 00:05:00,333
Leorio: Die, you asshole!

95
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,536
- ( Hunters cheering )
- Killua: Wow.

96
00:05:02,569 --> 00:05:06,573
By the looks of it, this clip
must have had a big impact.

97
00:05:06,607 --> 00:05:09,443
He seems fine
using his nen ability in public.

98
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:10,811
- ( Punch thumps )
- Die, you asshole!

99
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:12,379
Killua: Guess he’s an emitter.

100
00:05:13,447 --> 00:05:14,782
So, what,

101
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:16,650
do people really hate gon’s dad?

102
00:05:16,683 --> 00:05:19,719
’cause that got
a standing ovation.

103
00:05:19,753 --> 00:05:21,955
- Piyon: Wowwee!
- ( Cell phone ringing )

104
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:24,859
I don’t think anybody
could have seen that one coming!

105
00:05:28,562 --> 00:05:30,531
Gotoh: Master illumi.

106
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:31,865
( Amane grunts )

107
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:39,506
Gotoh: Yes, at once.

108
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:41,308
Just a moment, please.

109
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:52,886
Killua: Thanks, gotoh.

110
00:05:55,622 --> 00:05:58,358
I finally have
all the information I need.

111
00:05:58,392 --> 00:06:02,963
Now I know how each family
member feels about alluka.

112
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:04,931
♪

113
00:06:07,401 --> 00:06:08,802
Despite what he says,

114
00:06:08,836 --> 00:06:11,339
I know my father
still trusts me.

115
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:14,441
If he didn’t,
he would have tried to stop me,

116
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:17,677
and he wouldn’t have
let me bring gotoh along.

117
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:20,681
However, he’s wary
of alluka’s ability,

118
00:06:20,714 --> 00:06:22,082
which makes perfect sense,

119
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:24,551
given that,
with just one wrong move,

120
00:06:24,585 --> 00:06:27,321
the whole family could die.

121
00:06:27,354 --> 00:06:31,658
On the other hand, he obviously
wants to control alluka’s power.

122
00:06:31,692 --> 00:06:33,494
Why else would he
decide to lock her up

123
00:06:33,527 --> 00:06:34,928
in a room filled with toys?

124
00:06:34,962 --> 00:06:36,363
That must be it.

125
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:38,665
I can’t think
of any other reason.

126
00:06:38,699 --> 00:06:40,668
That’s why he had
his most trusted butlers,

127
00:06:40,701 --> 00:06:44,572
tsubone and amane,
accompany us on this mission.

128
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:48,008
If something happens, they can
bring us back immediately.

129
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:50,443
And he hopes they’ll be able
to gather some hints

130
00:06:50,477 --> 00:06:51,845
that’ll help him control alluka.

131
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:55,616
Tsubone and amane understand
their roles in his plan,

132
00:06:55,649 --> 00:06:59,520
and, as a result,
they’re being overly cautious.

133
00:06:59,553 --> 00:07:01,789
Gotoh and canary
are being subtle about it,

134
00:07:01,822 --> 00:07:03,957
but I can tell
they’re on my side

135
00:07:03,991 --> 00:07:05,993
and they’re trying to help us.

136
00:07:06,026 --> 00:07:08,629
♪

137
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:16,337
And then there’s illumi.

138
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,809
I could feel
amane’s tension spike

139
00:07:21,842 --> 00:07:24,945
at the exact moment
his name was mentioned.

140
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:26,847
That can only mean one thing.

141
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:30,851
Amane and tsubone and father
and grandpa, by extension,

142
00:07:30,884 --> 00:07:32,853
must disagree with illumi.

143
00:07:34,655 --> 00:07:36,157
If I had to guess,

144
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:38,859
i’d say illumi’s plans
for alluka are...

145
00:07:41,762 --> 00:07:45,065
Good job, gotoh.
That was a great play.

146
00:07:45,098 --> 00:07:47,934
You threw out his name
to fish for amane’s reaction.

147
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:51,905
If tsubone were here,
i’m sure she would have noticed

148
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:54,742
gotoh’s subtle reaction
when he answered the phone,

149
00:07:54,775 --> 00:07:56,810
and she’d have
tried to distract me

150
00:07:56,844 --> 00:07:59,714
or signal amane
to shut off her emotions.

151
00:08:03,584 --> 00:08:06,987
This is a family disagreement,
an intra-family mission.

152
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:10,924
Whenever the members
of the zoldyck family

153
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,893
differ in their opinions
or objectives,

154
00:08:12,926 --> 00:08:15,796
they’re each encouraged
to do things their own way,

155
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:18,865
rather than attempt to unite
around the same common goal.

156
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,601
It’s a contest!

157
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:26,106
Father and grandpa want alluka
to stay close to them

158
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:29,109
so they can control her,
and, besides that,

159
00:08:29,142 --> 00:08:31,911
they don’t want me
to get hurt by her ability.

160
00:08:33,113 --> 00:08:36,583
There are
just two things I want...

161
00:08:36,617 --> 00:08:38,052
To save gon...

162
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:41,155
And to give alluka her freedom.

163
00:08:42,222 --> 00:08:45,592
♪

164
00:08:45,626 --> 00:08:46,927
And illumi...

165
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:50,431
I know what he wants, too.

166
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,902
He wants to kill alluka.

167
00:08:55,969 --> 00:08:57,103
Illumi: This killua?

168
00:08:57,137 --> 00:08:59,039
Killua: That’s right.

169
00:09:01,742 --> 00:09:04,211
Illumi: You removed the needle,
didn’t you?

170
00:09:05,579 --> 00:09:09,016
Killua: I did.
I feel better now.

171
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:12,819
Illumi: Then I won’t have
to hold back when I kill you.

172
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:16,056
Killua: Kill me? Seriously?

173
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:19,627
( Illumi chuckles )

174
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:23,164
You can’t kill family members
during an intra-mission.

175
00:09:24,865 --> 00:09:26,967
I’d never kill family.

176
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:32,072
Alluka: Isn’t it great, amane?

177
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:34,574
This part,
it’s really interesting.

178
00:09:34,608 --> 00:09:36,043
♪

179
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:39,980
I don’t get why this story
is so mysterious.

180
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:46,820
Killua: What dad said before...

181
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:49,589
Is this what he meant?

182
00:09:51,225 --> 00:09:55,563
Silva: It is not
a member of the family.

183
00:09:55,596 --> 00:09:56,764
( Teeth grind )

184
00:09:56,797 --> 00:09:58,198
( Nen whooshes )

185
00:09:58,232 --> 00:10:00,101
Killua: They’re just
a bunch of bullies...

186
00:10:01,668 --> 00:10:03,970
Every last one of them.

187
00:10:04,004 --> 00:10:05,172
( Cell phone cracks )

188
00:10:05,205 --> 00:10:06,973
Then bring it on.

189
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:09,510
I’ll beat you at your own game.

190
00:10:19,286 --> 00:10:22,189
Illumi: Right. Then let’s begin.

191
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:35,269
( Tires squealing )

192
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:51,819
♪

193
00:10:51,852 --> 00:10:54,755
Gotoh: Master killua,
hold on tight to master alluka!

194
00:10:54,788 --> 00:10:56,757
Killua: Yeah! I got it!

195
00:10:56,790 --> 00:11:00,260
Gotoh: If you two are
ever more than a meter apart,

196
00:11:00,294 --> 00:11:02,663
amane will capture
master alluka,

197
00:11:02,696 --> 00:11:05,365
and tsubone will
take you back home by force!

198
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:07,134
♪

199
00:11:23,116 --> 00:11:24,217
( Killua gasps )

200
00:11:45,239 --> 00:11:46,407
( Killua grunting )

201
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:49,143
( Gotoh grunts )

202
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:56,149
( Explosion )

203
00:11:57,451 --> 00:11:59,153
Hisoka: Oh, dear.

204
00:12:11,832 --> 00:12:14,301
Hisoka: Well, that was
quite extreme, wasn’t it?

205
00:12:14,334 --> 00:12:17,237
I thought you were
going to ask him first.

206
00:12:17,271 --> 00:12:21,742
Illumi: I have a spy who’s
been feeding me information,

207
00:12:21,775 --> 00:12:24,878
and, upon further analysis,

208
00:12:24,912 --> 00:12:28,249
there’s something
that just doesn’t add up.

209
00:12:28,282 --> 00:12:29,850
Hisoka: Hmm?

210
00:12:29,883 --> 00:12:32,986
Illumi: Killua’s been
hiding rules from me.

211
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,256
( Wind blowing )

212
00:12:35,289 --> 00:12:38,159
If there are rules
I don’t know about,

213
00:12:38,192 --> 00:12:39,894
trying to negotiate with him

214
00:12:39,927 --> 00:12:44,064
is pointless
and a complete waste of time.

215
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,299
It’s entirely possible
that killua

216
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:49,770
will accede to my demands
because they favor him.

217
00:12:49,803 --> 00:12:51,371
I must get rid of alluka

218
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:54,308
before he has a chance
to use that advantage.

219
00:12:54,341 --> 00:12:55,876
Hisoka: Oh?

220
00:12:55,909 --> 00:12:59,112
Illumi: I just need you
to eliminate the butlers

221
00:12:59,146 --> 00:13:01,915
and, at the same time,
look for an opportunity

222
00:13:01,949 --> 00:13:05,886
to separate alluka
from killua for now.

223
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,854
Hisoka: Okay.

224
00:13:07,888 --> 00:13:09,022
By the way...

225
00:13:10,324 --> 00:13:12,893
If I see killua
and there’s a chance,

226
00:13:12,926 --> 00:13:13,894
can I?

227
00:13:13,927 --> 00:13:15,095
♪

228
00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:17,864
( Birds squawking )

229
00:13:17,898 --> 00:13:20,033
Illumi: Hisoka,

230
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,702
I will kill you...

231
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:27,274
Right here, right now.

232
00:13:29,376 --> 00:13:31,445
Hisoka: That was just a joke.

233
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:37,184
Um, you’re oozing bloodlust
all over the place.

234
00:13:37,217 --> 00:13:38,418
Is that cool?

235
00:13:38,452 --> 00:13:39,420
( Killua gasps )

236
00:13:39,453 --> 00:13:42,189
Illumi’s bloodlust.

237
00:13:45,058 --> 00:13:47,360
Illumi: Oops! Well, damn.

238
00:13:48,795 --> 00:13:51,765
Did you do that on purpose?

239
00:13:51,798 --> 00:13:54,301
Hisoka: Of course not.

240
00:13:55,869 --> 00:13:57,771
If it’s at all possible,

241
00:13:57,804 --> 00:14:00,307
I would prefer gon to live, too.

242
00:14:02,309 --> 00:14:04,878
The more toys you have,

243
00:14:04,912 --> 00:14:07,715
the more fun, right?

244
00:14:09,516 --> 00:14:11,451
♪

245
00:14:14,321 --> 00:14:17,825
Well, only if it’s possible.

246
00:14:20,561 --> 00:14:23,998
Killua: It’s okay.
Your big brother’s got you.

247
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:26,500
Keep your eyes closed,
and don’t let go of me!

248
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:27,901
Alluka: Uh-huh.

249
00:14:27,935 --> 00:14:29,837
Amane: First things first.

250
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,972
Escape from master illumi.

251
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:34,007
If he knows the route
we’re taking,

252
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:36,210
it’s best to divert
as soon as possible.

253
00:14:42,349 --> 00:14:44,852
Killua: I agree, but still...

254
00:14:46,153 --> 00:14:47,988
It’s hard for me to trust you.

255
00:14:48,021 --> 00:14:49,923
You do realize that, right?

256
00:14:49,957 --> 00:14:53,828
Amane: My grandmother and I
are not your enemies, you know.

257
00:14:53,861 --> 00:14:55,529
Killua: Well,
maybe not at this very moment,

258
00:14:55,562 --> 00:14:58,532
but that could change,
along with dad’s mood.

259
00:14:58,565 --> 00:15:00,467
Amane: Master silva
and master zeno

260
00:15:00,501 --> 00:15:03,137
are not your enemies
any more than we are.

261
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:05,339
All of us share
exactly the same mission,

262
00:15:05,372 --> 00:15:07,341
and that is to bring you
back home safely,

263
00:15:07,374 --> 00:15:08,542
no matter what happens.

264
00:15:08,575 --> 00:15:10,310
♪

265
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:15,148
Killua: Yeah,
but if that mission

266
00:15:15,182 --> 00:15:16,850
doesn’t include alluka...

267
00:15:19,186 --> 00:15:21,488
Then all of you are my enemies.

268
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:24,191
Godspeed!

269
00:15:24,224 --> 00:15:25,492
Lightning speed!

270
00:15:30,998 --> 00:15:32,299
( Cell phone beeps )

271
00:15:32,332 --> 00:15:33,900
Gotoh: It’s me.

272
00:15:33,934 --> 00:15:36,136
There’s been
a slight change of plan.

273
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:37,905
We lost sight of killua.

274
00:15:39,406 --> 00:15:41,541
We need four vehicles now.

275
00:15:41,575 --> 00:15:43,844
We’ll follow the same route.

276
00:15:43,877 --> 00:15:47,547
If master killua contacts you,
follow his instructions,

277
00:15:47,581 --> 00:15:49,383
but avoid
any sensitive information.

278
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:52,586
Master illumi
knew right where we were.

279
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:56,189
A Butler or family member
must be helping him,

280
00:15:56,223 --> 00:15:59,526
so be sure to stay fully alert
until further notice.

281
00:16:00,594 --> 00:16:01,562
Man: Understood.

282
00:16:01,595 --> 00:16:02,529
( Cell phone beeps )

283
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,568
♪

284
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:25,152
Tsubone: Ah...

285
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:28,088
Look at that.

286
00:16:28,121 --> 00:16:30,357
The young master’s all grown up.

287
00:16:32,059 --> 00:16:34,295
If I hadn’t known
about that technique,

288
00:16:34,328 --> 00:16:37,031
I wouldn’t have
had time to react.

289
00:16:37,064 --> 00:16:40,034
He’ll make
an excellent assassin.

290
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:44,204
Oh, dear. It doesn’t take much
for me to tear up these days.

291
00:16:45,272 --> 00:16:46,673
In that case,

292
00:16:46,707 --> 00:16:49,410
he won’t let master illumi
get the better of him.

293
00:16:49,443 --> 00:16:51,412
Oops! I shouldn’t say that.

294
00:16:51,445 --> 00:16:55,482
I just find it difficult to
like masters illumi and milluki.

295
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:57,385
They take after their mother
too much.

296
00:16:58,485 --> 00:16:59,586
Now then...

297
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:02,223
Time to set aside
personal opinion.

298
00:17:02,256 --> 00:17:05,459
If he breaks the rules,
everything changes.

299
00:17:05,492 --> 00:17:10,063
I need to devise a way
to subdue master killua,

300
00:17:10,097 --> 00:17:11,532
and it’ll have to be something

301
00:17:11,565 --> 00:17:13,667
that takes his speed
into account.

302
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,202
All right, then.

303
00:17:19,306 --> 00:17:22,409
Killua: All right!
We’re real far away.

304
00:17:22,442 --> 00:17:24,678
Let’s just take a little break.

305
00:17:24,711 --> 00:17:27,681
I’d like to use
lightning speed to keep going,

306
00:17:27,714 --> 00:17:29,549
but, just to be
on the safe side,

307
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:32,352
I should save my energy
for getting into town.

308
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:36,022
- Alluka: Big brother...
- Killua: Huh?

309
00:17:38,325 --> 00:17:41,428
Alluka: Do you want me to go?

310
00:17:47,534 --> 00:17:52,039
Would you all get along better
if I just went away for good?

311
00:18:02,749 --> 00:18:04,417
Killua: Look, alluka...

312
00:18:06,186 --> 00:18:07,454
If I were...

313
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:14,561
The only person who really
loved you in the whole world,

314
00:18:14,595 --> 00:18:16,630
well, would that make you sad?

315
00:18:18,031 --> 00:18:19,533
What do you think?

316
00:18:19,566 --> 00:18:21,501
♪

317
00:18:29,576 --> 00:18:31,545
( Alluka sighs )

318
00:18:31,578 --> 00:18:33,680
( Giggles )

319
00:18:33,714 --> 00:18:36,317
( Sighs )

320
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:39,220
I think i’d be
so happy about that,

321
00:18:39,253 --> 00:18:41,155
i’d never stop smiling.

322
00:18:41,188 --> 00:18:43,057
Killua: Okay.

323
00:18:43,090 --> 00:18:45,159
I promise i’ll
always be there for you,

324
00:18:45,192 --> 00:18:47,027
no matter what happens.

325
00:18:50,197 --> 00:18:52,299
Don’t worry about anyone else.

326
00:18:52,332 --> 00:18:54,134
It’s just you and me.

327
00:18:55,802 --> 00:18:58,305
♪

328
00:19:00,507 --> 00:19:02,376
Someone’s there.

329
00:19:02,409 --> 00:19:04,144
Is it tsubone?

330
00:19:05,412 --> 00:19:06,446
Illumi?

331
00:19:07,614 --> 00:19:10,250
I guess this won’t be easy.

332
00:19:10,284 --> 00:19:11,318
Bring it on.

333
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,588
Let’s go.

334
00:19:15,622 --> 00:19:17,557
( Footsteps )

335
00:19:19,626 --> 00:19:21,128
Gotoh: Who are you?

336
00:19:22,429 --> 00:19:26,133
Hisoka: A magician
who prefers anonymity.

337
00:19:54,461 --> 00:19:55,529
Gotoh: Stay back, you two.

338
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:59,866
You shouldn’t even try
to take him on.

339
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,503
Just dodge him if you can,

340
00:20:02,536 --> 00:20:05,205
and save your energy
for the mission at hand.

341
00:20:06,473 --> 00:20:08,608
Go after master killua.

342
00:20:11,778 --> 00:20:13,346
( Coins jingle )

343
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,482
I’ll play with you.

344
00:20:15,516 --> 00:20:17,485
♪

345
00:20:17,518 --> 00:20:19,487
Hisoka: A power that lets you

346
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:22,623
rapidly fire coins
more powerful than bullets...

347
00:20:24,591 --> 00:20:26,493
Powerful enough to explain

348
00:20:26,527 --> 00:20:28,829
why you would send
your subordinates away.

349
00:20:30,197 --> 00:20:31,699
Gotoh: My coins
pack enough power

350
00:20:31,732 --> 00:20:34,835
that you can’t escape unscathed
if they hit.

351
00:20:34,868 --> 00:20:37,904
It must have something to do
with his ability.

352
00:20:37,938 --> 00:20:39,873
( Coins jingling )

353
00:20:41,942 --> 00:20:43,410
Hmm.

354
00:20:51,351 --> 00:20:53,720
Hisoka: I see you’re confused.

355
00:20:53,754 --> 00:20:56,857
My aura has qualities
of both gum and rubber.

356
00:21:02,396 --> 00:21:04,598
Gotoh: Showing
your hand already?

357
00:21:04,631 --> 00:21:07,334
You may regret that,
cheap conjurer.

358
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:10,804
Hisoka: What’s the point
in hiding things from the dead?

359
00:21:10,838 --> 00:21:13,541
It doesn’t matter
if you know my ability.

360
00:21:13,574 --> 00:21:15,543
( Gotoh grunts )

361
00:21:15,576 --> 00:21:17,378
( Hisoka chuckles )

362
00:21:17,411 --> 00:21:19,346
♪

363
00:21:20,881 --> 00:21:23,350
Narrator: Hisoka and gotoh

364
00:21:23,383 --> 00:21:27,520
are about to engage
in a fierce battle.

365
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,893
( Singing in Japanese )

